        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#JP">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><foreign xml:lang="la"><expan><abbr>D</abbr><ex>is</ex></expan> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>anibus</ex></expan> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>acrum</ex></expan> <g ref="#interpunct">·</g></foreign>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name>Κλωδία</name> <name>Βαλεντεῖνα</name></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/>χαῖρε <expan><abbr>ἔζη</abbr><ex>σεν</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>ἔ</abbr><ex>τη</ex></expan> <num value="40"><foreign xml:lang="la">XXXX</foreign></num>
                    <lb n="4"/>ἐποίησε ἰδίᾳ γυναι
                    <lb n="5" break="no"/>κὶ <persName type="attested"><name>Ἰγνᾶτις</name> <name>Κάρικος</name></persName>
                    <lb n="6"/><expan><abbr>μνή</abbr><ex>μης</ex></expan> χάριν
                    </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Text after Kaibel in IG</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>Sacred to the spirits of the underworld. Klodia Balenteina, farewell. She lived 40 years. Ignatis Karikos made this for his own wife, for the sake of her memory.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#JP">
                <p>The text is distinctive for a number of features illustrating linguistic interference from Latin: the use of the Latin abbreviated header DMS (with interpuncts according to the transcriptions, not used in the rest of the text); the use of Latin numerals in line 3; the use of abbreviations both for <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἔζη(σεν) ἔ(τη)</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="grc">μνή(μης) χάριν</foreign>. The unusual structure of the text (and use of χαῖρε which is not generally attested at Catania) further marks it out as distinctive, and Korhonen emphasises its extra-urban provenance.</p>
            </div>
